The Liverpool boss had led his team to 86 points and 89 goals from their 36 matches in 2021-22 so far, with the Reds beaten only twice as they compete with Manchester City for the title. Klopp is up against Thomas Frank (Brentford), Pep Guardiola (Manchester City), Eddie Howe (Newcastle United) and Patrick Vieira (Crystal Palace) for the honour, which he won in 2019-20. Fans can cast a vote for Klopp to win here before the deadline of 6pm BST on Monday May 16. -Advertisement- 